Yifeng County in Jiangxi Province is "one of homes of bamboo" in China. Looking down from the air, it feels like gliding on an emerald sea where Longxi Village is hidden. Local people have been living with bamboo for many years. Play the video to learn more. About 'Journeys in Nature': Jiangxi Yifeng Series Yifeng County in China's Jiangxi Province belongs to the subtropical warm and humid climate zone. Its average annual temperature is around 17.2 degrees Celsius. The county is known as one of homes of bamboo in China. Nearly one third of the county's area is covered by Moso bamboo forests. (Cover image via screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)